  "texts": [
    "In general we have Bσ, BBσ and BBBσ operators that we can consider where B are building blocks that start at linear order in π with the linear terms of the form π ′ or ∂ i ∂ j π.",
    "Clearly the operators we have above cannot come from BBBσ operators since they contain single spatial derivatives acting on a π.",
    "The Bσ option also cannot yield something parity-odd.",
    "We are therefore left with BBσ.",
    "Consider the first of the above dimension-10 operators."
  ],
